<p>Whenever I extract a zip file using the ZipArchive class in PHP, the character encoding for both folders and files from the zip turns up wrong. (In my case Scandinavian letters like æ ø å).</p>  <pre><code>$zip = new ZipArchive(); $res = $zip-&gt;open($target_path); if ($res === true) {     $zip-&gt;extractTo($extract_folder."/".$name[0]);     $zip-&gt;close();     unlink($target_path);     } </code></pre>  <p>The code works great for standard letters. Is there any way to specify encoding in this class? Or any alternative classes that do?</p>